    • Method Detail

      • getDnPattern

        public String getDnPattern()
        Determines the distinguished name (DN) pattern for a caller entry name.

        The value would be formatted like:
        "uid={0},ou=people,ou=myrealm,dc=base_domain"

        where the {0} would be substituted with the caller name.

        Returns:
        The distinguished name (DN) pattern for a caller entry name.

      • setDnPattern

        public LdapEntryMapping.CallerMapping setDnPattern(String dnPattern)
        Specifies the distinguished name (DN) pattern for a caller entry name. See getDnPattern() for pattern format.
        Parameters:
        dnPattern - The caller DN pattern.
        Returns:
        This CallerMapping instance, for additional configuration.
        See Also:
        getDnPattern()
